              <span><strong class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Step 1. Ground School.</strong> Learn the theory behind spins, including the aerodynamics and regulations involved. Understand the common causes of spins and the proper recovery techniques.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-x-3">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="mt-1 h-5 w-5 flex-none fill-sky-600" height="24" viewBox="0 -960 960 960" width="24"><path d="M160-80q-33 0-56.5-23.5T80-160v-480q0-33 23.5-56.5T160-720h160v-80q0-33 23.5-56.5T400-880h160q33 0 56.5 23.5T640-800v80h160q33 0 56.5 23.5T880-640v480q0 33-23.5 56.5T800-80H160Zm0-80h640v-480H160v480Zm240-560h160v-80H400v80ZM160-160v-480 480Zm280-200v120h80v-120h120v-80H520v-120h-80v120H320v80h120Z"/></svg>
              <span><strong class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Step 2. Flight Training.</strong> Conduct flights with an experienced instructor to practice spin entries, spins, and spin recoveries. Demonstrate your ability to recover from a spin safely.</span>
